---
const points = [
  {
    title: "Defensibility over magic",
    body: "Every estimate ships with the comps, weights, and adjustments. No black-box scores — only paper trails.",
  },
  {
    title: "Built on public records",
    body: "The data that informs property tax is already public. We do the unglamorous work of indexing, normalizing, and keeping it fresh.",
  },
  {
    title: "Designed for specialists",
    body: "Vental is opinionated. We're not a generic valuation platform — we're a tool for people who do this every day.",
  },
]
---

<section class="border-b border-border">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="grid gap-16 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.4fr] lg:items-start">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest text-muted-foreground uppercase"
        >
          Our mission
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance sm:text-4xl"
        >
          We're building the system of record for commercial property tax.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-10">
        <p class="text-lg text-pretty text-muted-foreground">
          Commercial property tax is one of the largest line items in real
          estate — and one of the most opaque. We started Vental because the
          process of producing a defensible estimate hadn't meaningfully changed
          in decades: spreadsheets, PDFs, and tribal knowledge.
        </p>
        <div
          class="grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-border bg-border md:grid-cols-3"
        >
          {
            points.map((p) => (
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-medium tracking-tight">{p.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
                  {p.body}
                </p>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
